@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml

left to right direction
title FIG-09-04. BPMN and DMN Responsibility Split

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 90
skinparam ranksep 70

package "BPMN process responsibility" as BPMN #F7F9FB {
  rectangle "Capture payment\ninstruction\n<<Process task>>" as Capture #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Determine Payment Route\n<<Business Rule Task>>" as RuleTask #EAF6E8
  rectangle "Route result?\n<<Gateway>>" as Gateway #FFFFFF
}

package "DMN decision responsibility" as DMN #F2F5F7 {
  rectangle "Payment inputs\namount, currency,\naccount status,\nscreening result,\ncut-off status" as Inputs #FFFFFF
  rectangle "Payment Routing Rules\n<<Decision logic>>" as Logic #EAF6E8
  rectangle "Determine Payment Route\n<<Decision>>" as Decision #DDEEFF
}

Capture --> RuleTask
RuleTask --> Decision
Inputs --> Decision
Logic --> Decision
Decision --> RuleTask
RuleTask --> Gateway

legend bottom
BPMN shows process order, responsibility and branching after the result.
DMN shows repeatable decision logic and returns a named route result.
The technical binding from a BPMN Business Rule Task to a DMN decision is vendor-specific.
endlegend
@enduml
